Goal:
The test checks the extent of support for the Performance Monitoring Unit as described in Section 22 and 23 of PRM-0.
ET-SOC does not have any support for User Performance Monitoring counters and as such those accesses should trap.
While ET-SOC does not support mhpmcounter9-31/mhpmevent9-31, these are hard-wired to 0 and so technically should not
trap if accessed from M-Mode (although the reads should always return 0).

Parameter(s):
Thread - This test will run on any Thread of any Core of any Neighborhood of any Shire depending on what is enabled.

Details:
Please note that ET-SOC does not support the Performance Monitoring Unit as described in the RISC-V privileged spec.
Section 23 specifically calls out the differences in the implementation.

